## Why this is the cleanest approach

1. **One source of truth** — uses the actual `client_reference_id` FK in the database, not heuristic string matching on `param_code`
2. **Includes generic rows** — `EQUITY`, `FUNDS`, `DEFAULT` params (where `client_reference_id IS NULL`) still work for all clients
3. **Cached per request** — `paramsByClient` map avoids hitting the DB once per security if multiple securities belong to the same client
4. **No code changes in `DemandHandlerImpl`** — the existing loop logic works correctly once the data is properly filtered upstream
5. **Future-proof** — when new Historical clients are added (TPA_H, ESY_H, etc.) no code changes needed

